Chain: pssk-cv-b2-260416-v9-260416-205922-7a1f

## Issues Found
1. [CRITICAL] Scope/i18n contradiction — The prompt says all work is limited to `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx` and external files outside `menuapp-code-review/` are inaccessible, but later makes 11 dictionary additions mandatory without naming a target file. In the actual source, `tr()` at `CartView.jsx:282-287` already falls back to the supplied Russian strings, so missing keys do not surface raw keys in this component. PROMPT FIX: remove the mandatory dictionary change, or provide the exact dictionary file path and explicitly widen scope. If dictionary sync is desired, make it a separate follow-up task.
2. [MEDIUM] New cancellation logic is weaker than the source logic — Fix 1 and Fix 4 instruct new totals/counts to filter only raw `o.status === 'cancelled'`, even though the existing file already normalizes cancellations through `getOrderStatus(...).internal_code` plus a raw fallback at `CartView.jsx:443-446` and `459-463`. That can miscount totals if cancellation is present only in normalized stage data. PROMPT FIX: add a shared `isCancelledOrder` helper that mirrors the existing predicate and reuse it in rendered-table totals, self totals, and any terminal predicates.
3. [MEDIUM] Optional-chaining verification grep is incorrect — The prompt tells the executor to use `grep -a -n "currentTable\\?\\."` and says it should match `currentTable?.name` / `currentTable?.code`. In GNU grep BRE, `\?` is a quantifier, not a literal `?`, so this can false-negative even though the real source has optional chaining at `CartView.jsx:385`. PROMPT FIX: use `grep -a -nF "currentTable?."` or `grep -a -nE "currentTable\\?\\."`.
4. [MEDIUM] Fix 3 treats an external close-session contract as verified when it is not inlined — The prompt claims `sessionOrders` becomes raw `status === 'closed'` after `closeSession()` from S286, but its own pre-review grep only proves `sessionOrders` exists. Because the prompt also says external files are inaccessible, the terminal predicate is partly speculative. PROMPT FIX: inline the authoritative `closeSession()` contract, or downgrade this to an assumption and require explicit runtime validation before approving the fix.
5. [LOW] R4 identity wording is inconsistent with the instructed storage key — R4 says `cv_terminal_dismissed_{tableId}`, while Fix 3 implements `currentTable?.name || currentTable?.code`. That fallback may be necessary because the source only exposes `name`/`code` at `CartView.jsx:385`, but the prompt never states whether this is an approved deviation or what happens if names/codes change. PROMPT FIX: explicitly bless `name || code` as the temporary surrogate key and note its limitations, or split stable-id plumbing into a separate scoped task.

